<div class="algorithm" data-algorithm="requestQuadLayer">
The <dfn method for="XRWebGLLayerFactory">requestQuadLayer(GLenum textureTarget, XRLayerInit init)</dfn> method creates a new {{XRQuadLayer}}.

When this method is invoked, it MUST run the following steps:

  1. Let |promise| be [=a new Promise=].
  1. If the device does not support the creation of {{XRQuadLayer}}, throw an {{NotSupportedError}} and abort these steps.
  1. Let |session| be the target {{XRWebGLLayerFactory}}'s [=XRWebGLLayerFactory/session=].
  1. Let |context| be the target {{XRWebGLLayerFactory}}'s [=XRWebGLLayerFactory/context=].
  1. If |session|'s [=ended=] value is <code>true</code>, [=reject=] |promise| with an {{InvalidStateError}} and return it.
  1. If |context| is lost, [=reject=] |promise| with an {{InvalidStateError}} and return it.
  1. Run the following steps [=in parallel=]:
    1. Let |layer| be a new {{XRQuadLayer}}
    1. Initialize |layer|'s [=XRQuadLayer/context=] to |context|.
    1. Initialize |layer|'s [=XRQuadLayer/session=] to |session|.
    1. Initialize |layer|'s {{XRLayer/colorTextures}} as follows:
        <dl class="switch">
         <dt> If [=XRQuadLayer/context=] is a {{WebGL2RenderingContext}} and textureTarget is {{TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY}}
         <dd> Initialize |layer|'s {{XRLayer/colorTextures}} to a |array| with a single new instance of {{WebGLTexture}} created as a texture array with |context| and |layerInit|'s {{XRLayerInit/alpha}} values.
         <dt> Else if textureTarget is {{TEXTURE_2D}}
         <dd> Initialize |layer|'s {{XRLayer/colorTextures}} to a |array| with 2 new instances of {{WebGLTexture}} created as 2D texture with |context| and |layerInit|'s {{XRLayerInit/alpha}} values.
         <dt> Otherwise
         <dd> [=reject=] |promise| with an {{InvalidStateError}} and return it.
         <dd> 
         </dl>
    1. let |depthsupport| be true if |context| is a {{WebGL2RenderingContext}} or the {{WEBGL_depth_texture}} extension is enabled in |context|.
    1. Initialize |layer|'s {{XRLayer/depthStencilTextures}} as follows:
        <dl class="switch">
        <dt> If |layerInit|'s {{XRProjectionLayerInit/depth}} or {{XRProjectionLayerInit/stencil}} are set and |depthsupport| is false
        <dd> [=reject=] |promise| with an {{InvalidStateError}} and return it.
        <dt> Else if |layerInit|'s {{XRProjectionLayerInit/depth}} and {{XRProjectionLayerInit/stencil}} are not set
        <dd> Initialize |layer|'s {{XRLayer/depthStencilTextures}} to an empty |array|.
        <dt> Else if [=XRQuadLayer/context=] value is a {{WebGL2RenderingContext}} and textureTarget is {{TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY}}
        <dd> Initialize |layer|'s {{XRLayer/depthStencilTextures}} to an |array| with a single new instance of {{WebGLTexture}} created as a texture array with |context| and |layerInit|'s {{XRLayerInit/depth}}, {{XRLayerInit/stencil}}, {{XRLayerInit/pixelWidth}}, and {{XRLayerInit/pixelHeight}} values.
        <dt> Else if textureTarget is {{TEXTURE_2D}}
        <dd> Initialize |layer|'s {{XRLayer/depthStencilTextures}} to an |array| with 2 new instances of {{WebGLTexture}} created as 2D texture with |context| and |layerInit|'s {{XRLayerInit/depth}}, {{XRLayerInit/stencil}}, {{XRLayerInit/pixelWidth}}, and {{XRLayerInit/pixelHeight}} values.
        <dt> Otherwise
        <dd> [=reject=] |promise| with an {{InvalidStateError}} and return it.
        </dl>
    1. Allocate and initialize resources compatible with |session|'s [=XRSession/XR device=], including GPU accessible memory buffers, as required to support the compositing of |layer|.
    1. If |layer|â€™s resources were unable to be created for any reason, throw an {{OperationError}} and abort these steps.
    1. [=/Resolve=] |promise| with |layer|.
  1. Return |promise|.

</div>

